The paper deals with the analysis of random number generators and entropy extractors, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of linear binary codes is also a common technique in coding theory (cs.DS) and error-correcting codes (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses the entropy rate of the output, which is a concept often studied in information theory and signal processing (cs.SI).
